Patient: What should I drink if I have heart failure?

Educator: Drink mainly water. Avoid sugary drinks, alcohol, and those with caffeine as they can cause dehydration.

Patient: How much water should I drink daily?

Educator: Try to limit to about 2 liters a day. Too much fluid can strain your heart.

Patient: But I get thirsty often.

Educator: Sip small amounts throughout the day. Chewing sugar-free gum or sucking on ice chips can also help.

Patient: It's hard to keep track of how much I drink.

Educator: Try using mobile apps or setting reminders on your phone to monitor your intake.

Patient: Why is this so important?

Educator: Monitoring your fluid helps control your heart health. Too much fluid can worsen your heart failure symptoms.